originalText.text:
I've seen Say What?! perform several times, and they are as funny as their name suggests. There's a great vibe at their shows too, which means that the shows are funny and a really fun place to be.

And hey, if you've got some courage, you can even volunteer to participate in one of their improv comedy games, like when they call audience members up to the stage to compete in their "rap battles." Or you can just sit back and let the pros take care of the hard stuff.

Either way, my advice to you: Steer clear of the local multiplex and its latest comedy dud, and drop by the next Say What?! performance and have some really big laughs.
